## Agent handoff

Use these repo-local Mantle skills. They are vendored copies of Core skills
from `@aotter/mantle`; `.mantle/*` files provide context, not a separate
skill contract.

- [`.agent/skills/mantle-develop/SKILL.md`](.agent/skills/mantle-develop/SKILL.md)
- [`.agent/skills/mantle-plugin/SKILL.md`](.agent/skills/mantle-plugin/SKILL.md)
- [`.agent/skills/mantle-theme/SKILL.md`](.agent/skills/mantle-theme/SKILL.md)
- [`.agent/skills/mantle-update/SKILL.md`](.agent/skills/mantle-update/SKILL.md)

First task after materialization:

```text
Read .mantle/launch-state.json, .mantle/features.json, and .mantle/handoff.md.
Run the local preview, open {{SITE_URL}}, and confirm the Worker boots. Then
inspect the already composed type manifest, homepage, and seed files before
making changes.
```

## Commands

- `pnpm dev` local preview on localhost:8787
- `pnpm validate` manifest validation
- `pnpm typecheck` TypeScript check
- `pnpm check` validate + typecheck
- `pnpm run deploy` deploy Worker after provider setup

Daily content authoring should use the Staff MCP endpoint at
`<SITE_URL>/mcp/staff`. Do not write directly to D1 or KV.

Media uploads are optional post-launch work. Do not set up R2 unless the
owner explicitly needs staff-managed images/files; R2 may require
Cloudflare billing or a credit card. When media uploads are needed, read
`node_modules/@aotter/mantle/docs/media-uploads.md` or
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aotter/mantle/develop/docs/media-uploads.md
and use Claude Code or another local/non-sandboxed coding agent. Do not
rely on Claude Cowork for R2 uploads.

## Notes

- This repo starts from the shared blank base; its selected type is already
  composed. Do not copy old full starter directories into it.
- Theme work happens later through `mantle:theme`; there is no launch
  theme picker.
- Kiwa source in this repo is copied source material. The repo must keep
  working without Kiwa registry access.
